$ %programfiles%\Microsoft SQL Server

This directory is the (default) *→ development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance root directory*. (At least, when using the
→ development/databases/SQL-Server installation center to install a new instance, it is referred to by that name).
-
It is also the (default) *shared feature directory*.

Some subdirectories are
table { ll
  Client SDK ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/version[`*version*`] ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/version/DTS[`*version*\DTS`] ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/version/R_SERVER[`*version*\R_SERVER`] ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/instance-id[`*instance-id*`] ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/MSSQLnn_INSTANCENAME[MSSQLnn.INSTANCENAME] ☰
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-SQL-Server/MSASnn_INSTANCENAME[MSASnn.INSANCENAME] ☰
table }

sa:
  The parent directory → Windows/dirs/Program-Files[`C:\Program Files`]
